1
00:01:29,460 --> 00:01:33,150
[Cage of Shadows]

2
00:01:33,550 --> 00:01:36,060
[Episode 15]

3
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:40,330
The outcome is decided.

4
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:42,560
Blue Team made a mistake
in their dance

5
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:44,820
and failed to complete the performance.

6
00:01:45,440 --> 00:01:46,720
This round

7
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:49,000
goes to Red Team.

8
00:01:49,479 --> 00:01:50,560
Great!

9
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:51,720
We won!

10
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:53,000
We won!

11
00:02:01,960 --> 00:02:02,680
Next

12
00:02:02,930 --> 00:02:04,160
is the second round

13
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:05,930
of the Hall of Elegance competition:

14
00:02:05,930 --> 00:02:07,180
Shi Qi.

15
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:10,030
Each team captain will appoint one person

16
00:02:10,050 --> 00:02:11,650
to finish this game of chess.

17
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:13,630
When playing,

18
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:15,240
before placing a piece,

19
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:18,460
you must state the corresponding number
and Chinese character

20
00:02:15,910 --> 00:02:16,890
[Home] [People] [Mountain]

21
00:02:16,980 --> 00:02:17,590
[Dynasty]

22
00:02:18,490 --> 00:02:20,410
for the intersection point

23
00:02:19,810 --> 00:02:20,730
[Star]

24
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:23,320
based on the vertical
and horizontal lines on the board.

25
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:21,640
[Star] [Wind] [Sky]

26
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:24,550
[Star] [Wind] [Sky]

27
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:26,160
A poem must be recited
before a piece is placed.

28
00:02:26,760 --> 00:02:29,820
Exceeding the time limit means a loss.

29
00:02:29,970 --> 00:02:32,840
Who can play such a complicated game?

30
00:02:32,860 --> 00:02:36,340
Didn't I say the captains would choose?

31
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:38,520
Isn't that a death sentence
for whoever volunteers?

32
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:39,810
Not necessarily.

33
00:02:40,130 --> 00:02:40,960
If you win,

34
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:43,079
you won't have to die.

35
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:46,960
Captain, don't pick me.

36
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:48,530
I don't know how to play chess.

37
00:02:48,530 --> 00:02:49,590
I don't want to die.

38
00:02:51,340 --> 00:02:52,920
Not only do you have to play chess,

39
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:54,650
you also have to recite poetry.

40
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:55,610
This is too...

41
00:02:58,320 --> 00:02:59,280
How about...

42
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:05,000
I'll do it.

43
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:05,760
Nan Yanzhi.

44
00:03:05,780 --> 00:03:06,580
Yanzhi.

45
00:03:06,950 --> 00:03:08,510
I can't let you do it.

46
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,200
Don't worry.

47
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,510
It just so happens

48
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,290
that I know a bit of both.

49
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,240
How could you compete yourself?

50
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,360
I said

51
00:03:45,620 --> 00:03:48,340
the captains choose the players,

52
00:03:49,190 --> 00:03:50,930
but I never said
they couldn't choose themselves.

53
00:03:50,930 --> 00:03:51,450
You...

54
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:53,800
We're doomed.

55
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,780
Now that President Wan steps
into the arena herself,

56
00:03:55,780 --> 00:03:57,840
isn't Yanzhi in grave danger?

57
00:03:59,329 --> 00:04:01,200
With voice-keeper stepping in personally,

58
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:02,910
it's certain death.

59
00:04:03,020 --> 00:04:03,820
Is that so?

60
00:04:03,850 --> 00:04:05,280
I beg to differ.

61
00:04:05,340 --> 00:04:06,600
I'll wager a thousand taels

62
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:07,400
Hmm.

63
00:04:07,660 --> 00:04:08,540
on her winning.

64
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:11,470
I want to meet someone.

65
00:04:11,490 --> 00:04:12,450
I heard

66
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,330
she is in your Lingya Tower.

67
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:17,070
When the time comes,
I'll use my wager as a signal

68
00:04:17,070 --> 00:04:19,040
to tell you who I want to meet.

69
00:04:23,830 --> 00:04:26,130
The second round of the Hall of Elegance,

70
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:27,080
Shi Qi,

71
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:29,370
officially begins.

72
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:35,120
White snow on the three rivers
returns to the green mound,

73
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:37,800
the endless Yellow River
winds around black mountains.

74
00:04:35,470 --> 00:04:37,000
[Snow] [Flower]

75
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,310
[Snow] [Three]

76
00:04:42,670 --> 00:04:44,300
[Snow] [Flower]

77
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:48,440
Don't blame me for not reminding you.

78
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:50,760
There is a time limit for making a move.

79
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:57,960
A timeout will result in a loss.

80
00:04:57,530 --> 00:04:59,020
[Si hour] [Wu hour]

81
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:06,010
Past glories of the Six Dynasties
fade with the river's flow,

82
00:05:06,010 --> 00:05:07,090
[Dynasty]

83
00:05:06,390 --> 00:05:08,470
leaving only cold mist and dying grass
in a stagnant green glow.

84
00:05:08,050 --> 00:05:09,430
[Six]

85
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,960
Seven or eight stars glimmer
beyond the sky,

86
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:16,410
two or three drops of rain fall
before the mountain.

87
00:05:16,410 --> 00:05:17,940
[Star]

88
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:20,330
How can she make every move so fast?

89
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:29,690
[Wu hour] [Wei hour]

90
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:35,920
A cup of wine to go with a brand new song,

91
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:38,920
The weather and pavilion
remain the same as last year.

92
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:41,460
If Yanzhi takes this long every time,

93
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:42,510
will she lose?

94
00:05:42,570 --> 00:05:44,240
She is definitely going to lose.

95
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:45,800
President Wan designed this board.

96
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,820
She knows every poem

97
00:05:48,010 --> 00:05:49,760
corresponding to each character by heart.

98
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:52,190
How could a few cups of weak wine

99
00:05:52,050 --> 00:05:52,430
[Star] [Wind] [Sky]

100
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:53,610
withstand

101
00:05:53,630 --> 00:05:55,550
the rushing evening wind?

102
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:55,590
[Wind]

103
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:57,440
The year is drawing to a close tonight,

104
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,159
yet the wanderer is still miles from home.

105
00:05:59,159 --> 00:06:01,400
May snow still blankets
the Tianshan peaks,

106
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:03,560
No flowers bloom,
only the biting cold speaks.

107
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:05,640
If you resign now,

108
00:06:05,660 --> 00:06:07,380
I can let you choose how to die.

109
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:09,890
You'd better save it for yourself.

110
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:19,140
One flake, two flakes, three or four,

111
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:21,400
five flakes, six flakes, seven or eight.

112
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:23,960
Thousands, myriads, countless flakes,

113
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:25,690
flying into the plum blossoms,

114
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:28,720
vanishing from sight.

115
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:31,060
What kind of doggerel is this?

116
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:32,360
How can it count?

117
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,800
This is an imperial poem written

118
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,340
by His Majesty himself.

119
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:36,600
How could it not count?

120
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:37,159
Fine.

121
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:38,840
I'll let it pass.

122
00:06:39,159 --> 00:06:42,120
You're just clinging to your last breath.

123
00:06:44,659 --> 00:06:47,040
A thousand fathoms of iron chains
sink to the riverbed,

124
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:50,040
a banner of surrender rises
from Stone City overhead.

125
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:55,520
Sure enough.

126
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,760
How could these female prisoners

127
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:58,850
outsmart voice-keeper?

128
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:00,520
-The game is not set yet.
-That is right.

129
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:03,360
It's still uncertain who will win.

130
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:06,760
The seven-string zither plays a cold,
desolate sound,

131
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:09,760
true understanding
of this art has rarely been found.

132
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:19,170
My victory is certain.

133
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:22,460
One more move and she loses.

134
00:07:29,450 --> 00:07:31,670
[Hai hour]

135
00:07:43,450 --> 00:07:45,450
We first met when we were young.

136
00:07:45,650 --> 00:07:47,060
You were fifteen.

137
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:48,610
I was seventeen.

138
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:04,580
Consider yourself lucky.

139
00:08:14,220 --> 00:08:15,220
Time's up.

140
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,720
President Wan ran out of time!

141
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:19,120
So Nan Yanzhi won?

142
00:08:19,230 --> 00:08:20,430
This round,

143
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:22,650
you win.

144
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:23,720
Ah!

145
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:24,970
-We won!
-We won!

146
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,090
We won!

147
00:08:26,170 --> 00:08:27,270
-We won!
-We won!

148
00:08:27,310 --> 00:08:28,670
We won!

149
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:33,650
Weren't you supposed to die if you lost?

150
00:08:33,650 --> 00:08:34,179
Yeah.

151
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,860
How can you just kill people randomly?

152
00:08:35,860 --> 00:08:36,929
The loser

153
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:40,000
just needs to pick someone to die for her.

154
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:43,120
As long as someone dies, it's fine.

155
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:47,160
How could voice-keeper lose?

156
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:49,750
Could the women
from Lingya Tower play dirty?

157
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,850
Since ancient times,
gamblers must accept their losses.

158
00:08:51,850 --> 00:08:53,110
Are you going

159
00:08:53,140 --> 00:08:55,540
to renege on a promise with me,
a weak woman?

160
00:08:56,730 --> 00:08:57,530
Humph.

161
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,160
Today,

162
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:07,070
we've fought two consecutive rounds,

163
00:09:07,070 --> 00:09:08,530
with each side winning one.

164
00:09:08,530 --> 00:09:10,970
I'm sure everyone is exhausted.

165
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:13,120
Let's call it a day.

166
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:15,520
Go back and rest.

167
00:09:15,820 --> 00:09:17,420
We'll fight again tomorrow.

168
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:19,230
The final result

169
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:23,320
will be decided
by tomorrow's ritual archery.

170
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:24,650
President Wan,

171
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:27,000
what are the details of the third round?

172
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,760
Please explain everything at once.

173
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:29,360
That way,

174
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,240
we can rest easy.

175
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:35,990
You can rest assured.

176
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:37,670
Tomorrow's third round

177
00:09:37,690 --> 00:09:40,200
will take place
in full view of the public,

178
00:09:40,230 --> 00:09:42,530
competing in ritual manners
and archery skills.

179
00:09:42,530 --> 00:09:43,440
How can these two

180
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,640
be competed simultaneously?

181
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:47,170
The Red and Blue Teams will
each choose four people.

182
00:09:47,170 --> 00:09:49,700
Two of them will be dressed
in full ceremonial attire

183
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:52,030
to perform the ritual of bowing to Heaven.

184
00:09:52,390 --> 00:09:54,460
The other two stand on the opposite side

185
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:55,890
holding feathered arrows,

186
00:09:55,890 --> 00:09:58,760
aiming at the jewels
adorning their teammates' hairpins.

187
00:09:58,760 --> 00:10:00,200
Shooting our own people?

188
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:01,140
Exactly.

189
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:02,840
The ritual performers

190
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,610
will each hold a bowl of dew.

191
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:06,510
When the arrow is shot,

192
00:10:06,530 --> 00:10:10,050
Any body movement
results in a one-point deduction.

193
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:13,640
If dew spills from the bowl,
two points are deducted.

194
00:10:13,660 --> 00:10:15,740
If there are mistakes in the ritual,

195
00:10:15,770 --> 00:10:17,270
five points are deducted.

196
00:10:17,510 --> 00:10:19,060
If the jade bowl breaks,

197
00:10:20,380 --> 00:10:22,780
you'll lose the competition immediately.

198
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:25,610
What if we accidentally
hit our teammate?

199
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:28,290
Then you can only
consider yourself unlucky.

200
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:31,520
But there are also bonus points
for shooting well.

201
00:10:31,980 --> 00:10:32,880
How?

202
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:36,040
Each archer has three arrows.

203
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:38,860
Hitting a jewelry
on the ritual performer's head

204
00:10:38,860 --> 00:10:40,130
adds five points.

205
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:43,400
How do we decide who performs the ritual
and who holds the bow?

206
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:44,330
By drawing lots.

207
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,130
President Wan,

208
00:10:45,130 --> 00:10:46,370
I have a request.

209
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:47,060
Speak.

210
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:49,410
Since the rules are clear,

211
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:51,640
I request President Wan

212
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:53,050
to draw lots now.

213
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:54,160
Alright.

214
00:10:54,570 --> 00:10:55,910
As you wish.

215
00:10:56,590 --> 00:10:57,790
Let's choose people.

216
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:02,200
Just the four of you.

217
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:06,760
We've made our choice.

218
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:07,740
What about you?

219
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,850
Since you guys know each other,

220
00:11:13,850 --> 00:11:15,580
you must have better teamwork.

221
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:16,760
Yes, exactly.

222
00:11:17,160 --> 00:11:17,850
You guys go ahead.

223
00:11:17,850 --> 00:11:18,850
You guys go ahead.

224
00:11:19,050 --> 00:11:20,030
Count me in.

225
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:24,640
Okay.

226
00:11:25,610 --> 00:11:27,410
Now we have exactly four people.

227
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:29,240
Somebody!

228
00:11:35,750 --> 00:11:37,410
[Shoot]

229
00:11:37,660 --> 00:11:39,450
[Ritual]

230
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:40,960
Now that the lots are drawn,

231
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:44,460
everyone go back and prepare.

232
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:46,130
See you tomorrow.

233
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:52,120
I wonder what tricks Wan Hongliu

234
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:54,000
will play tomorrow.

235
00:11:55,230 --> 00:11:56,960
I read the rules for the third round.

236
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:59,480
Yanzhi has already made it clear
with President Wan.

237
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:01,740
I suppose she won't play any more tricks.

238
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:03,560
Hard to say.

239
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:05,880
How could someone used to playing dirty

240
00:12:05,880 --> 00:12:07,520
suddenly become honest?

241
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:10,010
What's going on?

242
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:11,160
Is it Wan Hongliu?

243
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:14,000
You stay here and protect them.

244
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,460
I'll go out and take a look.

245
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:43,590
Nan Yanzhi.

246
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:46,880
Who are you?

247
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:49,020
How do you know my name?

248
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:51,240
I once bought your life
at the Lingya Tower casino.

249
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:53,130
Of course I know who you are.

250
00:12:54,030 --> 00:12:54,890
Bought my life?

251
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:59,400
So you are from the higher-ups.

252
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:01,430
I wouldn't have thought
that a seemingly gentle

253
00:13:01,430 --> 00:13:03,560
young lady like you

254
00:13:03,580 --> 00:13:06,640
could also be a devil
who treats human lives like grass.

255
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,720
But we have never met before.

256
00:13:09,220 --> 00:13:10,860
Never met before?

257
00:13:12,980 --> 00:13:14,350
If it weren't for you,

258
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:16,450
my husband wouldn't have died.

259
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,230
Your husband?

260
00:13:22,110 --> 00:13:24,440
You beheaded him
and abandoned his body in the wild.

261
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:26,040
Have you forgotten all this?

262
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:31,430
Only those on death row
would be brought to Lingya Tower.

263
00:13:31,430 --> 00:13:32,830
How did you sneak in here?

264
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:34,920
The newly appointed top scholar

265
00:13:34,920 --> 00:13:36,260
was beheaded and dumped outside the city.

266
00:13:36,260 --> 00:13:37,960
The killer hasn't been caught yet.

267
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:39,980
I went to the authorities
to turn myself in

268
00:13:39,980 --> 00:13:41,310
and took the blame.

269
00:13:41,420 --> 00:13:44,850
Your husband was the new top scholar,

270
00:13:44,880 --> 00:13:45,920
Shen Nian'an?

271
00:13:46,010 --> 00:13:47,150
You remember now?

272
00:13:48,970 --> 00:13:50,060
I didn't kill him.

273
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:52,880
I only took the blame for the killer

274
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:54,940
so that I could get into Lingya Tower.

275
00:13:55,290 --> 00:13:57,070
Do you think I would believe you?

276
00:13:57,070 --> 00:13:58,850
Everyone avoids Lingya Tower
like the plague.

277
00:13:58,850 --> 00:14:01,650
You would confess to a capital crime
just to get in?

278
00:14:08,760 --> 00:14:09,720
Sometimes,

279
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:12,020
the more dangerous the place,

280
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:14,260
the deeper the truth is hidden.

281
00:14:14,260 --> 00:14:16,080
I don't believe your nonsense.

282
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:16,960
Today,

283
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:18,360
I will avenge my husband

284
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:19,920
with my own hands!

285
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:21,120
Wait.

286
00:14:22,350 --> 00:14:23,970
I've seen his body.

287
00:14:23,990 --> 00:14:25,720
He was killed with a single strike.

288
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:27,560
The wound on his neck is clean,

289
00:14:27,560 --> 00:14:29,240
caused by a sharp, heavy weapon.

290
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:31,450
How could a woman like me

291
00:14:31,470 --> 00:14:32,810
manage that?

292
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:34,560
Moreover,

293
00:14:34,990 --> 00:14:36,190
before he died,

294
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:39,160
the tendons in his wrists and ankles
were severed.

295
00:14:39,160 --> 00:14:40,360
This wasn't merely murder.

296
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:41,760
It was an act of vengeance.

297
00:14:41,760 --> 00:14:43,220
Think about it carefully.

298
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:44,500
Who could possibly

299
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:46,560
hate him that much?

300
00:14:47,290 --> 00:14:48,080
So much

301
00:14:48,890 --> 00:14:50,810
that they wanted to make him
unable to even beg for death?

